            <!--Simple Verse. Delete this <div/> if not used.-->
            <div type="poem">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1826-27" script="print" medium="pencil"/>Title of Poem</head>
                <lg type="stanza" rhyme="aa">
                    <l>FAIR wood of the birches all waving around</l>
                    <l>And where the wind plays with its sighing sound</l>
                    <l>Blowing among the waving trees</l>
                    <l>That move so swiftly to the breeze</l>
                    <l>Now comes the sun! stay the flash is o'er,</l>
                    <l>And the blazing orb is seen no more</l>
                    <l>And the shade it is dark</l>
                    <l>Throwing gloom to the heart.</l>
                    <l>There the silvery trunks of the birches appear</l>
                    <l>And whistles the wind to the listening ear.</l>
                    <l>Yes wood of birches graceful fair</l>
                    <l>Waving in the gentle air</l>
                    <l>Growing so thick no light can come</l>
                    <l>And baffled is the fiery sun</l>
                    <l>Save where surrounded by the trees</l>
                    <l>Unmoved by the flying breeze</l>
                    <l>A monument of stone is found</l>
                    <l>Erected on the ferny groud</l>
                    <l>To Lady Catherines memory</l>
                    <l>And where the breeze sighs heavily</l>
                    <l>As if lamenting for the righteous dead</l>
                    <l>Sleeping full quiet on her narrow bed</l>
                
                </lg> 
            </div>
            <!--Simple Drama. Delete this <div/> if not used.-->
            
